<H2><A NAME=SECTION00128500000000000000> 35, 25 View</A></H2>
<P>
	<A NAME=plane-35a HREF="plane-35abig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="plane-35a.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="plane-35abig.gif">Figure (plane-35a): An Oblique 35,25 View of the Coordinate Axes</A>
<P>
	<A NAME=plane-35b HREF="plane-35bbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="plane-35b.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="plane-35bbig.gif">Figure (plane-35b): Translating in the 35,25 View</A>
<P>
<tt><em>Select ``35,25'' in the Button menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>sed x</em> <BR><em>Select ``Translate'' in the Solid Edit menu</em> <BR>mged&gt;
</tt>
<P>
	<A HREF="plane-35abig.gif">Figure (plane-35a)</A>
 is the 35,25 view of the axes model.
The axes are no longer 
parallel or perpendicular to the viewing surface or to the graphics tablet.
Edit changes using the graphics tablet will affect all of the coordinates of
the solid, in a manner that is visually intuitive when the solid
is moved around on the screen.
Select different points on the tablet with the mouse and notice the 
changes in the coordinates, such as in 
	<A HREF="plane-35bbig.gif">Figure (plane-35b)</A>
.
Note how all three components of the V vector have changed.
<P>
<em>Select ``REJECT Edit'' in the Button menu</em>
	<HR>

